parsed.explanation: The XML required both structural and content corrections. Structurally, a nested <BIBL> tag was closed correctly, and a typo in a closing tag (</PRIBL> was changed to </BIBL>) was fixed. The inconsistent tag <PRICE> was standardized to <PRIZE>. Content corrections involved fixing numerous corrupted characters (e.g., replacing sequences like '\u221a\u00fc' and '\u221a\u2264' with 'ß' and 'vo.' respectively, and correcting 'Anf\u221a\u00a7ng' to 'Anfang' and 'Gespr\u221a\u00a7ch' to 'Gespräch'). The word 'W\u221a\u00barmen' was corrected to 'Würmern' based on the likely historical context of the title. Extraneous noise characters ('\u221a\u2020') appearing before prices were removed.
